cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with monocular depth estimation from stereo-based self-supervision, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of self-supervised learning using depth hints. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of AI models for depth estimation. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as depth estimation is an important task in robotics for navigation and obstacle avoidance. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of computer vision models for depth estimation, which is a subfield of CVPR.
